import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='count', bins=50, color='blue')
    plt.axvline(data['count'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label='Mean Count: {:.2f}'.format(data['count'].mean()))
    plt.axvline(data['count'].median(), color='green', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label='Median Count: {:.2f}'.format(data['count'].median()))
    plt.legend()
    plt.xlabel('Count')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of flight counts between origin and destination airports?', wrap=True)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    top_10_airports = data.groupby('origin')['count'].sum().sort_values(ascending=False).head(10)
    top_10_airports_df = pd.DataFrame({'origin': top_10_airports.index, 'count': top_10_airports.values})
    sns.set(style="whitegrid")
    ax = sns.barplot(x="origin", y="count", data=top_10_airports_df, palette="Blues_d")
    ax.set(xlabel='Airport', ylabel='Total Number of Flights')
    for index, row in top_10_airports_df.iterrows():
        ax.text(index, row['count'], row['count'], color='black', ha="center")
    plt.xticks(rotation=45, ha='right')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    sns.set(style="whitegrid")
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(15, 10))
    sns.boxplot(x="count", data=data, orient="h", color="skyblue")
    ax.axvline(data['count'].mean(), color='r', linestyle='--', label='Mean')
    ax.legend(loc='best')
    plt.title('What is the average number of flights between origin and destination airports?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Count')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    sns.set(style="whitegrid")
    chart = sns.barplot(x="origin", y="count", data=data, palette="Blues_d")
    chart.set_xticklabels(chart.get_xticklabels(), rotation=90)
    chart.axhline(y=data['count'].mean(), color='r', linestyle='--', label='Mean')
    plt.legend(loc='upper right')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of flights between different origin airports?', wrap=True)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```
